The structure characterists of S-GQDs were investigated using TEM, AFM and XPS. TEM images revealed that S-GQDs were well-dispersed (Fig. 2
                        A) with relatively uniform size distribution. The average diameter of the S-GQDs was calculated to be 2.5nm (inset of Fig. 2A). High resolution TEM (HRTEM) image (Fig. 2B) showed clear lattice structure of the S-GQDs, further confirming that the S-GQDs have a high crystallinity. The lattice spacing was measured to be about 0.22nm that was consistent with the [1120] lattice fringes of graphite[32]. The AFM image showed the morphology and the height of the S-GQDs. Results indicated that the average height was 0.8nm (Fig. 3
                        ). Considering the doping of S atom and −COOH functionalization, a single-layer graphene structure was revealed.
